FT  12 FEB 93 / Tough targets for job training
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TOUGH targets for placing long-term unemployed people into jobs or training
have been set by the government for its new jobplan workshops, Lisa Wood
writes.
The week-long workshops, which will be mandatory for people who have been
unemployed for 12 months and longer, will be able to recommend the
withdrawal of unemployment benefits for individuals who are unwilling to
participate.
Jobplan is part of the government's strategy for tackling the rise in
long-term unemployment.
Training and Enterprise Councils, which manage training programmes in
England and Wales, fear that the targets will result in the Employment
Service, which runs Jobplan, referring unsuitable candidates to the new
Training for Work Scheme. From April this will offer training and work
experience to the unemployed.
