<HEADLINE>
FT  12 FEB 93 / World Trade News: US slaps 70% tariff on 'dumped' UK steel
rails
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NANCY DUNNE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE US Commerce Department yesterday levied duties of almost 70 per cent on
steel rail found to have been 'dumped' by British Steel and other UK
companies into the US market.
However, before the duties are made permanent, the International Trade
Commission must determine that dumping - selling at less than either the
cost of production or the product's cost in a third market - has injured US
companies. The injury test is more difficult to prove than dumping.
The steel rail complaint was filed by a division of Bethlehem Steel and CF&amp;I
Steel.
US imports of steel rail from the UK totalled Dollars 16.2m (Pounds 10.7m)
in 1991.
