<DATELINE>
   PHNOM PENH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
President Francois Mitterrand of France with the Cambodian head of state,
Prince Norodom Sihanouk, in Phnom Penh yesterday. Mr Mitterrand was the
first French leader to visit France's former colony since Charles de Gaulle
came in 1966, writes Victor Mallet in Phnom Penh. Mr Mitterrand appealed to
Cambodia's rival political factions to abide by a peace agreement signed in
Paris in 1991 and warned them not to disrupt or challenge the results of the
UN-sponsored elections in May. The peace accords have been undermined by
continued fighting between Khmer Rouge guerrillas and the
Vietnamese-installed government, and by the refusal of the Khmer Rouge to
participate in the elections or allow UN forces into its territory.
