<HEADLINE>
FT  11 FEB 93 / World Trade News: Argentina-Chile oil pipeline construction
begins
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LESLIE CRAWFORD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Construction began this month on a 425km oil pipeline that will link oil
fields in southern Argentina to Chilean refineries in the southern ports of
Talcahuano and San Vicente, Leslie Crawford writes.
The Dollars 300m project is being built by the two state oil companies, ENAP
of Chile and YPF of Argentina, and by Banco Rio de la Plata, an Argentine
bank. The pipeline through the Andean mountains is the first project of its
kind between the two neighbouring countries. It is expected to reduce
Chile's oil import bill by cutting transport costs - ENAP now imports oil
from Africa.
The pipeline will also allow Argentina to ship oil to the Far East from
Chilean ports on the Pacific Ocean.
</TEXT>
