FT  11 FEB 93 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
STRONG overseas demand for gold shares boosted activity in the sector and
the index ended 99, or 11 per cent, ahead at 990, but off the day's high of
1,011. Some analysts reported that new US buyers had come into the market,
attracted by the cheap levels of gold stocks. Vaal Reefs rose R17, or 10.4
per cent, to R180. The overall index put on 68 at 3,542 and industrials
added 36 at 4,645.
