<HEADLINE>
FT  11 FEB 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Last week's accelerating decline in Australian wool prices went further this
week, with a new low point for the present selling season reached on every
day. The Australian Wool Corporation's market indicator was 457 cents a kg.
on February 10, 31 cents or 6% lower than a week before. The lowest point
reached in the previous 1991-92 season was 434 cents a kg. These are
seriously uneconomic prices for most growers and some are withdrawing their
wool at reserve prices of their own, or withdrawing it immediately prior to
the auction.
